HEADWORD: Symbranchii
<hw>Sym*bran"chi*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ a gill.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of slender eel-like fishes having the gill openings
confluent beneath the neck. The pectoral arch is generally attached to
the skull, and the entire margin of the upper jaw is formed by the
premaxillary. Called also <altname>Symbranchia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symmetral</ent>⟦br⟧
